INTRODUCTION
In today’s quickly changing digital economy, modelling and planning are crucial skills for creating and executing successful technology driven companies. The complexity of operational and strategic decision-making increases significantly as organisations use automation, intelligent systems and data-driven infrastructures. In this scenario, modelling becomes an essential analytical tool that helps organisations simplify and organise complex real-world systems. Before allocating resources to real-world execution, decision makers can use modelling to investigate alternate scenarios, test hypotheses, forecast system behaviour under various circumstances and identify possible risks and ineffictiveness. This minimises expenses, lowers uncertainty and promotes evidence based decision making. 
Planning organises work, assigns resources, establishes deadlines and connects technology projects with more general business goals. Planning and modelling work together to guarantee that creative solutions are not only technically possible but also long-term sustainable, scalable and economically practical.
Inorder to modernise and improve traditional vending activities, this report introduces Smart VendAI, a advanced vending machine business concept that combines artificial intelligence(AI), machine learning (ML) and internet of things (IoT) technologies. Traditional vending machines are often limited by outdated manual procedures, delayed supply decisions, ineffective stocking procedures and a lack of real-time monitoring. These restrictions often results in overstocking, stockouts, higher operating expenses and lower customer satisfaction. Inorder to create a responsive and adaptable vending ecosystem, Smart VendAI uses intelligent data processing, automated inventory tracking and continous sensor monitoring. Smart VendAI reduces waste and increases profitability by using machine learning models and predictive algorithms to forecast product demand, optimise stock levels, and enhance replenishments schedules. Real-time data collection also allows for active maintanence, quicker decision making and better customer satisfaction through increased system dependability and product availability. 
The report shows how the design, assessment and validation of the SmartVendAI business concept are supported by conceptual modelling, business modelling, regression forecasting and simulation. Feedback loops, stock and flow relationships and long term behavioural trends within the system can all be clearly visualised. By showing how operational choices affect performance over time, this modelling technique improves strategic planning, enhancing overall business planning quality and allowing well informed data-driven decision making.

1.LITERATURE REVIEW
Modelling plays a fundamental role across engineering, computing, management science and operations research. Models provide simplified representations of complex systems, allowing analysis without the cost, risk or impracticality of testing in real-world scenarios (Pidd, 2009).
For business concept development, tools such as the Business Model Canvas helps us to identify key components of a business such as customers, value propositions, resources and revenue streams highlighting risks and guiding strategic refinement (Osterwalder & Pignueur, 2010).
Forecasting methods like regression analysis are essential for predicting future trends. Regression is effective for identifying relationships between variables such as customer footfall and vending sales and enables evidence based planning (Field,2018).
Simulation is equally important. It enables experimentation with dynamic systems without financial risks (Banks, 2010). Insight Maker, a popular system dynamics and agent based modelling tool, supports casual loop diagrams, stock and flow modelling and long term behaviour simulation, making it ideal for inventory, supply chain and operational forecasting.
System dynamics modelling provides information about long term patterns and feedback loops (Sterman, 2010). Using Insight Maker for Smart VendAI allows modelling of stock behaviour, demand variability and operational delays, ensuring decisions are based on system wide understanding.
Overall, modelling and planning frameworks provide a structured foundation for evaluating and developing Intelligent Vending Machine solutions like Smart VendAI.

  
2.OVERVIEW OF THE BUSINESS IDEA
2.1Business Concept
Smart VendAI is a AI powered vending solution that maximises product stocking and customer satisfaction by using machine learning algorithms and Internet of Things sensors. In contrast with traditional devices, Smart VendAI is able to:
Forecast demand patterns.
Automate Restocking alerts.
Real-time dashboard access to managers.
Minimise excess inventory and stockouts.
Customise product offering for each location.
Smart VendAI uses both software( AI forecasting, cloud dashboards) and  hardware(sensors, processors, connectivity modules) to increase operational insight, profitability and efficiency.

2.2Problems Solved
Traditional vending machines suffer from:
Unpredictable stock levels due to manual checks.
Limited data insight into consumer behaviour.
Non-customised product selection.
Subjective location decision lacking data.
High operational labour costs.
Smart VendAI solves these problems using automated monitoring, predictive analysis and location specific recommendations, enabling better cost control and improved customer experience.

2.3Business Value Offered
Smart VendAI offers:
Accurate demand forecast.
Fewer stockouts.
Reduced labour costs.
Increased revenue through data-driven product placement.
Enhanced customer satisfaction.
Competitive technological advantage.
These benefits make Smart VendAI  attractive to gyms, offices, transport hubs, universities, hospitals and commercial property owners.


