8.SIMULATION FOR INVENTORY PLANNING
8.1Scenario Setup in Insight Maker
Insight Maker was used to simulate Smart Vend AI’s stock behaviour using a stock and flow model.
Scenario variables:
Machine capacity - 300 items
Avg. Daily demand - 40 items
Supplier lead time - 3 days
Reorder point - 120 items

Figure 7

8.2Simulation Results
Initial inventory of 300 units declines steadily reaching almost -2000units by the end representing a net decrease.
Inventory falls below zero earlier in the simulation, which indicates 100% depletion of available stocks.
Daily demand increases from 10 to over 25 units showing an increase of more than 150% over the simulation horizon.
The reorder point and restock rate increases with demand.
Replenishments remains are insufficient resulting in a structurally unstable inventory system.
Current replenishment parameters fail to keep up with the growing demand, suggesting substantial upward adjustments for inventory stability.

